{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "The LORD Challenges Job"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then the LORD answered Job out of the whirlwind and said:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“Who is this who obscures My counselby words without knowledge?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Now brace yourself like a man; I will question you, and you shall inform Me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Where were you when I laid the foundations of the earth? Tell Me, if you have understanding."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who fixed its measurements? Surely you know! Or who stretched a measuring line across it?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "On what were its foundations set, or who laid its cornerstone,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "while the morning stars sang together and all the sons of God shouted for joy?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who enclosed the sea behind doorswhen it burst forth from the womb,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "when I made the clouds its garment and thick darkness its blanket,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "when I fixed its boundaries and set in place its bars and doors,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and I declared: ‘You may come this far, but no farther; here your proud waves must stop’?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "In your days, have you commanded the morningor assigned the dawn its place,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "that it might spread to the ends of the earth and shake the wicked out of it?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The earth takes shape like clay under a seal; its hills st and out like the folds of a garment."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Light is withheld from the wicked, and their upraised arm is broken."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Have you journeyed to the vents of the seaor walked in the trenches of the deep?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Have the gates of death been revealed to you? Have you seen the gates of the shadow of death?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Have you surveyed the extent of the earth? Tell Me, if you know all this."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Where is the way to the home of light? Do you know where darkness resides,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "so you can lead it back to its border? Do you know the paths to its home?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Surely you know, for you were already born! And the number of your days is great!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Have you entered the storehouses of snowor observed the storehouses of hail,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "which I hold in reserve for times of trouble, for the day of war and battle?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "In which direction is the lightning dispersed, or the east wind scattered over the earth?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who cuts a channel for the floodor clears a path for the thunderbolt,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "to bring rain on a barren land, on a desert where no man lives,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "to satisfy the parched wasteland and make it sprout with tender grass?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Does the rain have a father? Who has begotten the drops of dew?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "From whose womb does the ice emerge? Who gives birth to the frost from heaven,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "when the waters become hard as stone and the surface of the deep is frozen?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can you bind the chains of the Pleiadesor loosen the belt of Orion?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "32",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can you bring forth the constellations in their seasons or lead out the Bear and her cubs?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "33",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do you know the laws of the heavens? Can you set their dominion over the earth?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "34",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can you command the cloudsso that a flood of water covers you?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "35",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can you send the lightning bolts on their way? Do they report to you, ‘Here we are’?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "36",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who has put wisdom in the heart or given understanding to the mind?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "37",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who has the wisdom to count the clouds? Or who can tilt the water jars of the heavens"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "38",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "when the dust hardens into a mass and the clods of earth stick together?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "39",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can you hunt the prey for a lionessor satisfy the hunger of young lions"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "40",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "when they crouch in their dens and lie in wait in the thicket?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "41",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who provides food for the ravenwhen its young cry out to God\nas they wander about for lack of food?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}